<section id="about">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2>About Me</h2>
      <p>A career dedicated to psychiatric care, medical education, and leadership</p>
    </div>
    <div class="about-content">
      <div class="about-text">
        <p>
          I am a Consultant Psychiatrist at <strong>Mersey Care NHS Foundation Trust</strong>, one of the largest trusts
          providing physical health and mental health services in the North West of England, serving more than
          1.4 million people across Halton, Warrington, Knowsley, Liverpool, Sefton, and St Helens.
        </p>
        <p>
          As <strong>Director of Medical Education (DME)</strong> at the Trust, I oversee the training and development
          of psychiatric trainees, working closely with Liverpool Medical School and Edge Hill University Medical School
          to ensure the highest standards of clinical education.
        </p>
        <p>
          I also serve as <strong>Associate Dean</strong> and <strong>Chair of the General Adult Specialist Advisory Committee (GA-SAC)</strong>
          at the Royal College of Psychiatrists (RCPsych), where I contribute to shaping the future of psychiatric training
          and education across the United Kingdom.
        </p>
